{
  "stem": "2723.3",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And, um, I formed a relationship in the search of love, I think, totally disastrously expecting one person to be able to, um, at age 23, be everything that I lost.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was a doomed relationship because it was in the dream world sort of set-up that I had lived in, in that other world that wasn't really the one that I came back to.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And when that relationship, after a very brief marriage, broke up, um, I realized that staying in Slovakia was my biggest problem because I was continuously reminded of that which had gone on.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was no grave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I didn't have the luxury of my mother, who for every little bit of grief, had a grave to go to, her father's and her mother's.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I just had nothing to hang anything onto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Um, I felt that being divorced was a stigma I couldn't live with.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I felt totally unable to face life there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And contrary to my previous attitude to leaving Czechoslovakia for Australia, which my ex-husband then had wanted to do and did do-- he left and came to Australia-- I couldn't bear the thought of leaving my father once again.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We had just managed to get close.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it was again my personal grief that brought me into his-- his arms.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "In a way, my-- my, uh, divorce and pain at losing a relationship opened up my father and me for each other.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So I guess that was a kind of balance.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
